In the aftermath of the battle and with the reclamation of Kohlingen, many people came together to carve the names of friends and loved ones who lost their lives in the Fall. Locals and foreigners, rich and poor, noble and commonfolk all came together here as brothers and sisters in spirit to honor and remember the fallen.

All around this wall, thousands of names are carved into the surface. It stands now as a sacred Memorial wall.
